RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEEWINOT PASS settled off the pace between foes, split rivals at the eighth pole then rallied to get up in time. DADASHEV prompted the pace three wide and continued willingly to the finish. WE BE THERE raced wide throughout, loomed a stretch threat but was outfinished. OUCH OUCH OUCH alternated for the lead outside to midstretch and faltered. SINGINTHRUTHESTORM led then dueled inside, lost the whip at the five sixteenths pole and weakened. DANGNABBIT hesitated at the start, moved up inside then faltered. LOAD UP MOE lagged far behind then trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PARX RACING RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 28000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS OR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since June 25 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAYTOWN controlled the pace, repelled a challenge, widened briefly in midstretch and held on gamely. BEYOND BEST stalked the loose pacesetter three wide, went after the winner on the final turn then made gradual late gain just missing. GRAND PICK reserved inside, bid closer before half a mile then faltered. FICTIONALFAIRYTALE clipped heels and bobbled badly causing his rider to lose his irons on the first turn, rider got back in irons about an eighth of a mile later and was no factor. BATTUTA D'ORO dropped back outside, remained wide and had no response. REX KWON DO dropped back in the opening quarter inside, angled wide on the final turn and was no factor. TITANIUM RECKAGE had his heels clipped on the first turn and stopped abruptly. The stewards posted an inquiry into the incident on the first turn.
